</head>

<body>
    <main>
        <div class="container">
            <!-- Codrops top bar -->
            <div class="m_c">
                <h1 class="main_title">TeamQall</h1>
                <p class="main_text">Your team needs you</p>

                <a href="https://slack.com/oauth/authorize?scope=bot&client_id=2160160398.61870653398"><img class="but" alt="Add to Slack" src="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack.png" srcset="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack.png 1x, https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack@2x.png 2x"></a>
            </div>
            <section class="rw-wrapper">
                <h2 class="rw-sentence">
					 
					<br />
					<span>Your participation is needed in a game of</span>
					 
					<div class="rw-words rw-words-1">
						<span>Football</span>
						<span>Basketball</span>
						<span>PingPong</span>
						<span>Hockey</span>
						<span>Rugby</span>
						<span>Polo</span>
					</div>
				</h2>

            </section>

            <!-- --------------SCROLL BUTTON-------------- -->
            <div class="span"><span></span></div>
        </div>
        </div>
        <section class="faq">
            <h1 class="faq_title">Faq</h1>
            <div class="mc2 ">
                <h1 class="main_title2"> What is TeamQall?</h1>
                <p class="main_text2">Teamqall is a Slack bot - Queiroz - responsible to manage and organize team's periodic sport events.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="mc2 ">
                <h1 class="main_title2"> 
          How does it work?</h1>
                <p class="main_text2">
                    Our bot, Queiroz, will ask everyone interested in participating in our sport events if they will play in the next game. If someone doesn't answer, that person will be asked again later. This proccess will keep going until a proper answer is provided.
                </p>

            </div>
            <div class="mc2 ">
                <h1 class="main_title2"> 
          How often will I be asked?</h1>
                <p class="main_text2">
                    If you answer right away, only once!
                </p>

            </div>
            <div class="mc2 ">
                <h1 class="main_title2"> 
           Will I be bored by Queiroz, even if I am not interested in any events?</h1>
                <p class="main_text2">
                    No. By default, Queiroz will only target users in a designed channel - the channel where the event is planned. However, even the users in that channel will be asked beforehand if they want to answer Queiroz in the future.
                </p>


            </div>
        </section>

    </main>
</body>

</html>